Components and literals derived from ECC
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Re-expressed in Python (pattern reuse; no verbatim copy):

  * Data-home resolution (MANTHANA_DATA_HOME) — re-expressed from
    scripts/lib/agent-data-home.js into
    agent/src/manthana/agent/datahome.py.

  * Collector / adapter-registry pattern — re-expressed from
    scripts/lib/session-adapters/{registry,canonical-session,claude-history}.js
    into collectors/src/manthana/collectors/base.py.

  * State-store entity definitions — schemas/state-store.schema.json is the
    starting point that Manthana's schema package (schemas/src/manthana/schemas/)
    extends with the Turn / Session / Compaction entities.

Copied verbatim (with a per-file attribution comment at the copy site):

  * Secret / approval-command / sensitive-path detection literals
    (SECRET_PATTERNS, APPROVAL_COMMANDS, SENSITIVE_PATHS) — copied from
    scripts/hooks/governance-capture.js. [lands in Phase 3 — redaction]

  * Model cost RATE_TABLE and transcript token-summation logic — copied from
    scripts/hooks/cost-tracker.js. [lands in Phase 4 — compactor/cost]

  * State-store layer pattern (SQLite local + Postgres server) — re-expressed
    from scripts/lib/state-store/{schema,migrations,queries,index}.js.
    [lands in Phase 1 — local store]

Entries marked "[lands in Phase N]" are planned imports tracked here so the
attribution exists before the code does; each will carry its own per-file
attribution comment when written.
